	<div class="rails">
		<%= image_tag("rubyrails.jpg", class: "rpic") %>
		<p class="stackheader">Ruby on Rails</p>
		Ruby on Rails was used on this project because of its back end framework capabilities. Although we could have done much of what was done with Rails, we used Javascript for it's practicality and ease.
	</div>

	<div class="rails">
		<%= image_tag("js.png", class: "rpic") %>
		<p class="stackheader">Javascript</p>
		The star of the show. Javascript was used for the transistion between parts of the forms, the button highlighting and of course, the ajax. A few little nik naks were used with Javascript but overall, front end functionality, Javascript
	</div>

	<div class="rails">
		<%= image_tag("htmlcss.png", class: "rpic") %>
		<p class="stackheader">HTML/CSS3</p>
		Styles,styles and more styles. CCS3 made our page what it is. From the sleak grey background to the frames that hold the events. Not any HTML element or tag was left untouched by CSS.
	</div>

</div>

